{"questionId":"9518","questionHtml":"<p>Explain why <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;must have opposite signs.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{a^2} + bc < 0 \\Rightarrow bc < 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> so&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;must have opposite signs&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9518","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.1b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Explain why b and c must have opposite signs.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}